</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="139.[151,1436,1260,1357]" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,406,1295,1320]" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Name derivation.</emphasis>
The generic name 
<taxonomicName box="[620,766,1297,1320]" class="Insecta" family="Coccidae" genus="Mariacoccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="139" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis box="[620,766,1297,1320]" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Mariacoccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is composed of 
<taxonomicName box="[949,1019,1297,1320]" class="Pteridospermopsida" family="Peltaspermaceae" genus="Maria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Peltaspermales" pageId="139" pageNumber="140" phylum="Gymnospermophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[949,1019,1297,1320]" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">Maria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-, taken from 
<taxonomicName box="[1172,1239,1295,1320]" class="Pteridospermopsida" family="Peltaspermaceae" genus="Maria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Peltaspermales" pageId="139" pageNumber="140" phylum="Gymnospermophyta" rank="genus">Maria</taxonomicName>
in Rio de Janeiro State, Brazil, and - 
<taxonomicName box="[359,435,1333,1356]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Coccus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="139" pageNumber="159" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[359,435,1333,1356]" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="140">coccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, Latin (masculine, meaning a grain or seed), a name commonly used for scale insects.
</paragraph>
